<br>
1) Tag a mob with something. I use HoS. Do not use boastfull bellow or a snare. Throwing something works just as well but might require practice to time.<br>
<br>
2) The instant your spell/ranged attack lands you fade. Do not dealy! Do not drag the mobs around, at least not until you master the basics. (Dragging mobs around causes them to stack. See below.)<br>
<br>
3) The instant your fade pops off use bellow on the mob you want to pull.<br>
<br>
Speed is the important part here. You must chain the fade and bellow as fast as you can. Delay <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>will</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> cause the pull to fail. Even a half second delay can mess up everything.<br>
<br>
Another thing, this won't work when mobs are stacked on each other. They can be very close to each other, just not on top of each other. If the mob you are pulling paths over or near another mob it will agro. Its much harder to pull a mob several feet behind another mob this way. Possible but harder.<br>
<br>
<br>
Tag/fm/tag can sometimes be the best or only way to split mobs if a mob is immune to run speed changes, too high or immune to mezz or lull, too magic resistant, or all of the above. (Time tier3 boss split, or SolB/Permafrost giants for example.) It can be done in very limited spaces with practice. Its quick, taking only three seconds. No waiting on mobs to path away. With a throwing attack to start the first tag the execution time can be reduced to less then a second.<br>
<br>
The only drawback is the use of mana. In OoW zones the mobs can sometimes poof on the fade no matter how fast you are. (RS is where most poof on fade happens to me.)<br>
